            <div corresp="#c0071f2">
                <head>Amoor River, Asiatre Russia.</head>
                <p>Collins not established. Traveled through the Amoor Region only by permission of
                    Russia.</p>
                <p>He left Moscow Dec. 1856, traveled through the Region and reached San Francisco
                    Dec. 14, 1857.</p>
                <p>Agt. Collins left New York for St. Petersburg Sept. 4, 1858; arrived St.
                    Petersburg Sept. 28, 1858; left St. Petersburg Nov. 1859.</p>
                <p>Collins sailed from New York Sept. 28, 1859 - was in St. Petersburg May, 1860,
                    and in Washington Dec. 21, 1860.</p>
                <p>" " " " Aug. 2, 1862 - " " " " Oct. 1862 &amp; took charge of Consulate at St.
                    Petersburg</p>
                <p>as " " " " Vice Consul Nov. 7, 1862, served until Jan. 1863?. Went to London Aug.
                    1863 in behalf of his scheme for a telegraph line from Russia to America, via
                    Bering Straits. Left London arrived in New York Mar. 1, 1864. Left N.Y Sept. 21,
                    1864 for St. Petersburg. Arrived back in New York April 1865.</p>
            </div>
